@node Autor "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Note from author:
@{fg text}    -----------------

    After a period of nine months, I am able to continue programming my MSX2
emulator, now with a high quality MSX2 emulation, but to enjoy this you need
a fast Amiga system.

    This  version  needs  the AGA chipset.  Version 2.2 was the last version
compatible  with  OCS/ECS chipset.  But future versions will (possibly) work
with OCS/ECS chipsets.  (MC68020+ required.)

    This new version works a lot better than old versions.  But, please THIS
IS an emulator, NOT a MSX2 computer.

    New features of this version:

    - Line Interrupt emulation.

    YES!!!, Only Amiga makes it possible!!!  Now you can play games like the
Aleste  saga,  Xevious, Mr.Ghost, Quarth, etc...  But CAUTION:  this needs a
fast  Amiga system to run well.  (PAL screen and MSX2 Sprites refresh at 2fr
is recommended.)


    - Sprites mode 2 emulation:

    Now MSX2 sprites are displayed with the right colours.

    There are 4 different settings for emulating the MSX2 sprites:

    -  OFF :  MSX2 Sprites are not emulated.
    - 1 Fr.:  1 frame.  (100% refresh) too slow!
    - 2 Fr.:  2 frames. ( 50% refresh) Recommended.
    - 3 Fr.:  3 frames. ( 36% refresh) For slow Amiga systems.

    Note:   MSX2  Sprites  make  the emulation slower.  For this reason some
games crash MSX2 emulation in 1fr.  mode.


    - Realtime emulations:

        - Line Interrupts
        - Hardware Scroll
        - Palette Changes
        - Sprites display on/off
        - X Adjust of screen


    - R-800 code supported, but not checked!!!!

    - Some Z-80A and VDP bugs fixed.

    - MSX Virtual Disk emulation.  (MVD:)

    - Cartridges emulation.  (Only Cartriges of 16/32Kb.)

    - Cheat mode to find/set pokes of lives, level, etc...

    - Save Screen or complete VRAM as IFF-ILBM.  (Manga rulez!)


    This is all for now.  I hope you will like my emulator!

    
    N.B.:   This  emulator makes use of real MSX roms which are copyrighted,
so if you use this software you should own a real MSX2.


                                         Juan Antonio Gómez Gálvez.

                                       (Barcelona May 27th, 1996)


    PS:  Only AMIGA technology makes it possible!


@endnode


@node Introduccio "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Introduction:
@{fg text}    -------------

    This program emulates a 8-bit MSX2 computer.

    Quality of emulation depends on the Amiga system that is used.

    This  program  does  not  multitask  and freezes the Operating System to
obtain  a  good  quality  emulation, programming directly the Amiga's custom
chips.

    THIS  SHAREWARE  VERSION is freely distributable and can be published in
magazines  and  other  circulation  forms.  Allways make sure that all these
files are included:

    AmiMSX2_v2.3              MSX2 Emulator.
    Keyboard.iff              Picture with MSX2 keys in the Amiga keyboard.
    MVD_Control               AmiMSX2 menu without MSX2 Emulation.

    MSX_Drivers/
     RAMSX:                   To mount a StaticRAD for MSX and Amiga.

    Docs/
     AmiMSX2_English.guide    This file.
     AmiMSX2_Dutch.guide      The guide file in Dutch
     AmiMSX2_Espańol.guide    The guide file in Spanish

    #?.info                   Workbench's icons.


@{fg highlight}    DISCLAIMER:
@{fg text}    -----------
    THE AUTHOR DOESN'T GUARANTEE THAT THIS PROGRAM EMULATES A FULL MSX2, AND
ACCEPTS  NO  RESPONSIBILITY  FOR  LOSS  OF DATA DERIVED FROM THE USE OF THIS
SOFTWARE...

@endnode


@node Requeriments "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Minimal Requirements:
@{fg text}    --------------------------

    - AMIGA computer with AGA chipset
    - MC68020+
    - DEVS:mfm.device           (For DiskDrives emulation)
    - DEVS:statram.device       (For RAMSX: drive emulation)
    - LIBS:stc020.library v3.0+
    - LIBS:asl.library
    - 3MB of memory (1Mb Chip)
    - PAL, NTSC or compatible monitor.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Extra requirements for real MSX2 emulation:
@{fg text}    ------------------------------------------------

    - MC68020 at 28Mz or faster Processor
    - 2Mb of 32-bit Fast memory

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Compatibility:
@{fg text}    -------------------

    - 100% compatible with MC68020/MC68030

    - Not totally compatible with MC68040

    -  90% compatible with MC68060

    Note:  Traza0 mode (T0, bit 6 of SR) does not work on MC68060.

@endnode


