@node Z80A "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Z-80A  (Processor):   Emulated at 98%.
@{fg text}    ------------------------

    All works correctly except this:

    - Flags N and H are not emulated
    - SP register cannot read from ROM!
    - Flag P is only emulated at instructions OR, AND, XOR
    - R register not emulated well

    Now the AMIGA can NEVER crash!

@endnode


@node Dibuixos "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    VDP  (Graphics chip):   Emulated at 85%.
@{fg text}    ---------------------

    All works correctly except this:

    * Sprites:
        - Expanded Sprites
        - Sprites Collisions

    * VDP Commands:
        - MULTI mode (Screen 3)
        - Vertical Screen adjust

    * MSX-Video:
        - XOR mode emulated as NOT
        - Line logical operators
        - Color search

@endnode

@node Soroll "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  PSG  (Sound Chip):   Emulated at 99%.   
@{fg text}    -----------------------

    It works correctly.


@{fg highlight}    <*>  SCC  (Sound Custom Chip):   Emulated at 98%.   
@{fg text}    ------------------------------

    Amiga cannot emulate it correctly:

    - The SCC chip has 5 channels and Amiga only 4, when it uses 5 channels,
channel 5 will not be emulated.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  SCC+  (Sound Custom Chip+):   Emulated at 98%.
@{fg text}    --------------------------------

    Emulation is equal to SCC.

@endnode

@node Jocs "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Joystick ports:
@{fg text}    --------------------

    Two  firebuttons  in  MSX are supported.  Left and Right Amiga keys work
like joystick second firebutton.

    A Joypad can be used.

    Amiga firebutton 1 = MSX firebutton 1
    Amiga firebutton 2 & 3 = MSX firebutton 2    

    Amiga A port = MSX B port
    Amiga B port = MSX A port

              (Joysticks emulated in registered versions only.)

@{fg highlight}    <*> Mouse:
@{fg text}    ----------

    MSX mouse is emulated in port A of MSX when Joystick 2 menu is disabled.

    Amiga mouse needs to be connected in port A of Amiga.

@endnode

@node Teclat "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Keyboard:   Emulated at 99%. 
@{fg text}    --------------

    MSX keyboard is the same as Amiga's except for the following keys:
    (English keymap only)

                          AMIGA       MSX
                         -------     -----
                            F6       SELECT
                            F7       STOP
                            F8       HOME/CLS
                            F9       INS
                           F10       DEL
                      Left ALT       GRAPH
                     Right ALT       CODE

                            ` ~      ń Ń  (In MSX2 ROM only)
                            DEL      MSX DEL or MSX Pause (optional)
                            [ {      Caps Lock.
                            < >      Caps Lock.
                            ç Ç      Dead key. (accents)
                            ] }      Dead key. (accents)

                     Left Amiga      JoyStick 1 - 2nd firebutton
                    Right Amiga      JoyStick 2 - 2nd firebutton

             CTRL+Left ALT+DEL       MSX Reset
             CTRL+Left ALT+HELP      MSX Hard Reset

                           HELP      Go to Workbench's menu. (Exit)


    Note:  Ń or ń is a Spanish letter.

@endnode

@node Disc "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Disk drive:   Emulated at 99%.
@{fg text}    ----------------

    For  a good emulation of MSX drives you need to mount PCx:  of the drive
that you are using.

    Note:  If PCx:  is not mounted 1DD MSX disks will fail!

    Make sure your disks have got a MSX boot to avoid a hang up when the MSX
is booting from a disk drive.  You can install it, using "MSX Boot" gadget.
    DO  NOT  INSTALL ALL DISKS you get, because some MSX disks had their own
boot  to  run the game.  Install only disks that you've formatted in a PC or
using PCx:  drives.

    To emulate MSX disk drives I have had to "kill" the interrupt that warns
the  Amiga  that  a disk has been changed, so when you exit the emulator the
diskdrive will not recognise Amiga disks.  I am sorry.

    But you can do this to recover Amiga drives:

    ASSIGN DFx: dismount
    MOUNT DFx:

    You need to do a mount-list with DFx:  datas.

@endnode

@node Altres "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Memory:
@{fg text}    ------------
    You can emulate from 128 to 4096Kb RAM amd 128Kb VRAM.

    Sub-Slots  (&HFFFF)  are  not  supported,  so there are NO COMPATIBILITY
PROBLEMS with Sony or Philips memory models!

    If you get an "out of memory" error, try to disable drive B:  emulation.

@{fg highlight}    <*>  Clock Battery:
@{fg text}    -------------------
    
    Correctly emulated except the time! 


@{fg highlight}    <*>  Printer port:   Emulated at 99%.
@{fg text}    ------------------

    Emulation by Sergi Martinez.  (I haven't got a printer!)

@endnode





@node incompatibilitat "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Errors and incompatibility:
@{fg text}    ---------------------------

    This  version  is  very  reliable,  if  a game does not work it can be a
general  MSX  incompatibility problem.  (Not all MSX games worked on all MSX
configurations.  Like with some Amiga software today.  (Ed.))

    If you run into an incompatibility problem try to do the following:

    - Set Disk-Drive B: ON or OFF.
    - Set RAM: to 256Kb.
    - Set DOS or DOS2.
    - Set Screen to PAL.
    - Set MSX2 Sprites to 2fr. or 3fr.

    If  it still not works, then sorry, wait for future versions or check it
in a real MSX2.

@endnode


@node Tecnics "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Technical data:
@{fg text}    ---------------

    This  program  was  developed  100%  in  assembly  language  on an AMIGA
1200+Blizzard 1220 (MC68020 at 28Mz and 4Mb of 32-bit Fast RAM).

    To  get  the  highest  possible  emulation  speed  this program disables
multitasking and programs the Amiga's custom chips directly.

    The MSX2 used for checking is a Philips NMS-8280 MSX2 computer.

    All sources of this emulator are designed and programmed by the author.


@{fg highlight}    <*> Slots Configuration:
@{fg text}    ------------------------

                       Slot 0  Slot 1  Slot 2  Slot 3
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|
               Page 0 | Bios  |       | Sub   |  RAM  |
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|
               Page 1 | Basic |       | Disk  |  RAM  |
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|
               Page 2 |       |       |       |  RAM  |
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|
               Page 3 |       |       |       |  RAM  |
                      |-------|-------|-------|-------|


@{fg highlight}    <*> Emulation speed:  (±5%)
@{fg text}    ---------------------------

              Setup             Time     Z-80A       %      Accelerator
      ----------------------   ------   -------   ------   -------------
      MSX2  Philips NMS-8280     864     3.5Mz     100%
      ----------------------   ------   -------   ------   -------------
      Amiga 1200/20  28Mz.       600     5.0Mz     144%    Blizzard 1220
      Amiga 1200/30  50Mz.       183     8.3Mz     236%    Blizzard 1230-IV
      Amiga 1200/60  50Mz.       136    22.2Mz     635%    Blizzard 1260
      ----------------------   ------   -------   ------   -------------

@endnode


@node Futur "AmiMSX2 Emulator."

@{fg highlight}    Future versions:
@{fg text}    ----------------

    Now,  because  of personal reasons I will spend less time on programming
the emulator.

    Because of this I don't know when I will end version 2.4.

    * Features for version 2.4:

    - MSX-Video   emulation   (MSX2  blitter)  in  real  multitasking  and
      super-optimized CPU-VRAM modes and vice versa.

    Untill this is done , some games like e.g.  Zanac-Ex won't work well.

    - 100% updating of VRAM (Amiga Bit-planes) in Screen changes.

    Untill this is done, some games like e.g.  Feed Back won't work well.


    * Plans for the more distant future:

    - Emulation of Graph 3 and 4 in real-time for a possible emulation of
      Space Manbow.

    - FM Pak emulation via MIDI.

    - Compatibility with OCS/ECS chipsets.

    - Compatibility with MC68040.

    - More compatibility with MC68060.

@endnode


